    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dear patient  
Thank you for taking the time to share your experience with us and I am sorry you had cause to attend the Minor Injuries Unit (MIU) at Bideford Hospital and that you experienced a lengthy wait to be fully reviewed. I am pleased you found that the quality of care which you received was good; however I am also sorry you were disappointed with the organisation of the unit. I hope that you are now recovering from your fall.  
I would welcome the opportunity to look into your concerns in order to provide you with a full investigation and response, and would ask that you either telephone or e-mail the Patient Advice &amp;amp; Liaison Service (PALS) on 01271 314090 or ndht.pals@nhs.net for further support.  
Kind regards  
Jayne&lt;/CommentText&gt;
